13/12/2005
BRUSSELS, Belgium -- During its meeting Monday (12 December), the EU General Affairs and External Relations Council praised the progress achieved by the Western Balkan countries in the EU integration process, as acknowledged in the latest country reports of the European Commission. 
The Council also strongly welcomed the recent capture of top Croatian indictee Ante Gotovina. 
It called on Serbia-Montenegro and Bosnia and Herzegovina (BiH) to intensify activities to bring remaining fugitives, including Radovan Karadzic and Ratko Mladic, to the UN war crimes tribunal for trial. 
Albania was urged to step up the fight against organised crime and corruption, and to implement electoral reform. 
BiH was urged to implement police sector restructuring and strengthen its legislative framework. 
(EU Web site - 12/12/05)
